id: pm-gbbn
title: Add operator-facing stale-lock cleanup to pm gc (locks scope)
description: "As an operator, I want pm gc to clean stale lock files, so that lock debris from crashed processes is removed without waiting for the next mutation"
type: Story
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:lock","area:storage",living-map,story
created_at: "2026-05-31T19:49:47.479Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-05T21:19:36.939Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: pm gc --scope locks removes only expired locks; --dry-run lists; default all-scope gc includes locks
parent: pm-o2kc
resolution: "Satisfied by the pm gc locks scope (pm-d70h): operators reclaim crashed-process lock debris immediately via pm gc / pm gc --scope locks instead of waiting for the next mutation of that item."
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-d70h,related,"2026-05-31T19:49:47.479Z",null,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-05T20:43:54.683Z",claude-code-agent,"DONE: src/core/lock/lock-gc.ts + tests/unit/core/lock/lock-gc.spec.ts created. Safety policy: any lock file that cannot be read or parsed is RETAINED (never deleted). Staleness uses lock-embedded ttl_seconds, not settings. Exported signature: runLockGc(pmRoot, {dryRun, now?, hooks?}) → LockGcResult with scanned/removed/retained/warnings/entries[]. StaleLockScanEntry has file/id/owner/created_at/ttl_seconds/age_seconds/stale/reason. LockGcHooks has onRead?/onWrite?. Edge cases covered: missing locks dir (ENOENT), non-.lock files ignored, active lock retained, expired lock removed (real unlink), dryRun preview, unparseable JSON retained+warning, invalid shape variants (missing id, bad ttl type, null ttl, array root, primitive root), invalid timestamp (NaN) retained+warning, zero ttl (immediately stale for positive age), negative ttl (always stale), onRead/onWrite hooks invoked + warnings surfaced, onWrite NOT called under dryRun, unlink ENOENT race treated as removed, unlink EPERM failure → lock_remove_failed + retained, readFile ENOENT ghost (disappeared after readdir) silently skipped, readdir non-ENOENT rethrown, deterministic now injection, sorted entries. npx vitest run passed: 27/27 tests, 100% lines/branches/functions/statements."
close_reason: "Satisfied by the pm gc locks scope (pm-d70h): operators reclaim crashed-process lock debris immediately via pm gc / pm gc --scope locks. Verified by manual e2e (stale removed, active+unparseable retained)."
